VenusOS-WiFiAP
==============

WiFi Access Point with 4G internet sharing for Venus OS on Raspberry Pi 3.

Creates a virtual ap0 interface on the BCM43438 chip and runs a full AP stack:
hostapd (WPA2), dnsmasq (DHCP), iptables NAT toward wwan0 (4G modem).

Compatible with VenusOS-E3372h (Huawei 4G modem package).

## Requirements

- Venus OS v3.50 or later
- Raspberry Pi 3 (BCM43438 WiFi chip)
- SetupHelper (kwindrem) installed
- hostapd installed: `opkg install hostapd`
- E3372h 4G modem connected on wwan0 (for internet sharing)

## Installation

Via SetupHelper PackageManager (recommended):
  GitHub: florent1080/VenusOS-WiFiAP

Manual:
  cd /data/VenusOS-WiFiAP && bash setup install auto

## Configuration

Edit /data/wifi-ap/wifi-ap.conf :

  SSID=ZeVan              # WiFi network name
  PASSWORD=victron1234    # WPA2 password (8-63 chars)
  CHANNEL=1               # WiFi channel (1-11)
  AP_IP=192.168.0.1       # RPi3 gateway IP
  UPSTREAM=wwan0          # Interface for internet sharing

After editing: svc -t /service/wifi-ap

## Connecting

- Connect your device to WiFi "ZeVan" (or your custom SSID)
- Your device gets IP 192.168.0.x via DHCP
- Internet via 4G (wwan0) — shared with NAT
- SSH to RPi3: ssh root@192.168.0.1

## Notes

- connman tethering is disabled on install (conflicts with ap0)
- The native /service/hostapd is disabled (hostapd-run requires serial-number absent on DIY RPi3)
- wifi-ap.conf is preserved on reinstall / Venus OS update
- Logs: tail -f /var/log/wifi-ap/current
